Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a raised central part surrounded by twisted string impressions. The side is covered with finger impressions. The top bears part of a seal-impression. On the right a tiny cartouche with a kheper at the top, rest not preserved. To the left of the cartouche a sun-disc and a further not recognisable sign
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
